//alogrithm
1. Convert the number into a string.
2. Traverse from right to left and find the first index `idx` such that `s[idx] < s[idx+1]`.
3. If no such index exists, print `-1` because no greater permutation is possible.
4. Traverse again from the right and find the first digit greater than `s[idx]`.
5. Swap this digit with `s[idx]`.
6. Reverse the substring from `idx+1` to the end to get the smallest greater number.
7. Convert the string back to a number.
8. If the number exceeds `2147483647`, print `-1`; otherwise print the number.


Overall: O(n)

Space:O(1)

Description

Sagar likes to solve tricky problems just like you. He was recently trying to solve a problem, could not solve it so he needs your help. Sagar has a positive integer and he wants to find the smallest integer which has exactly the same digits existing in the integer N and is greater in value than N. If there is no valid answer, print -1.

Note that the answer should fit in 32 bit integer, if there is a valid answer but does not fit in 32 bit integer, then print -1.

Input Format

The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases.

Each of the next T lines contains an integer N.

Output Format

For each test case, print the answer in a single line. If there is no valid answer or the answer does not fit in a 32-bit integer, print -1.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10^5

1 ≤ N ≤ 2^31 − 1

Sample Input 1

1
112

Sample Output 1

121

Sample Input 2

1
987654321

Sample Output 2

-1

Sample Input 3

1
89

Sample Output 3

98




#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

void solve() {
    string s;
    cin>>s;
    bool flag = false;
    int n = s.size();
    for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++)
    {
        if(s[i] < s[i+1])
        {
            flag = true;
            break;
        }
    }

    if(flag)
    {
        int idx = -1;
        for(int i = n - 1; i >0; i--)
        {
            if(s[i] > s[i-1])
            {
                idx = i - 1;
                break;
            }
        }
        int maxi = INT_MAX;
        int maxiidx = -1;
        for(int i = n - 1; i > idx; i--)
        {
            if(s[i] > s[idx])
            {
                maxiidx = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        swap(s[idx],s[maxiidx]);

        reverse(s.begin()+idx+1,s.end());
        long long num = stoll(s);

if(num > INT_MAX)
{
    cout << -1 << endl;
}
else
{
    cout << s << endl;
}
    }
    else
    {
        cout<<"-1"<<endl;
    }
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}
